title: For Sale:  Beautiful All-Matching 1909 M96 Swedish Mauser 6.5x55mm w/bayonet, sling, etc.
location: Grey Forest (NW of SA), San Antonio, Texas
postcontent: PENDING SALEOffered for sale is this beautiful 100+-year-old relic, that is as ready for action as the day it was built in the years before the First World War. Make no mistake, it shows some sign of its travels with dents and scratches in the stock and moderate wear in the metal finish, but everything is solid and there is no rust or cracks or anything that would be a functional problem anywhere I can find. I should point out that I am not a professional gunsmith, so I will recommend that if you intend to fire this rifle, it would be worthwhile to have it professionally inspected because of its age. I personally have never fired this rifle, but the previous owner did fire it plenty and said it was excellent at long range.When the Swedes made these, they serial numbered about every piece of metal on the gun, and every number matches – which means it is the same complete set of parts that was originally assembled into this weapon in 1909. I see the crown cartouche and serial number on the receiver (of course), bolt, extractor, bolt retainer, safety, firing pin, sling band, bayonet band, butt plate, floor plate, and three separate pieces in the rear tangent sight. Even the magazine follower has the cartouche on it, though no apparent serial number. The stock's serial number is not visible without disassembly, but it is cartouched.The barrel's serial number is not visible without disassembly. It is import marked "M96 SWEDEN 65X55", and on a line below that, "C.A.I. ST. ALB. VT." The barrel length is 29". It has very good rifling and no apparent muzzle erosion.The rear sight is an adjustable leaf, with marks up to "20", which probably is supposed to mean 2000m = about 1¼ mile — perhaps a little optimistic! The trigger is clearly a combat trigger, not a target trigger, but its break is quite crisp without any apparent creep. The stock and handguard are beautiful walnut, with marks, scratches and scuffs befitting its 100+ years, but I think it could be turned into a showpiece with a little work.The 6.5x55 round is one known for long range accuracy. Take a look at the Wikipedia description, en.wikipedia.org/wiki/6.5%C3%9755mm#Sporting_use if you are not already familiar. It was one of the first successes of a 6.5mm round, and of course you see more and more variants of those today.The rifle is about 49¾" long overall, and weighs about 9 pounds, 7 ounces unloaded, with the sling and cleaning rod.Included with the rifle are several accessories:- bayonet, scabbard and frog of the correct type that does fit on the weapon, but the serial number on the bayonet does not match the weapon.- cleaning rod that mounts in a slot under the barrel. This rod is of the correct type, but the serial number does not match the weapon. (Very common)- adjustable 1¼" wide leather sling with brass keepers and buckle. It is of the correct type for this weapon, but it is not possible to determine its authenticity – however I believe it could be original.Also available to the buyer of the rifle at additional cost are a supply of ammunition, and equipment and supplies to make more. Of course this is an unusual round, and while you can buy all the new ammo you need, it's a great round to handload:- 60 rounds of handloaded ammunition, marked with the load information. Of course even I would recommend caution with anyone else's handloads, but he was loading them for his own use, so I believe he used due caution. Of course they could always be pulled down and reloaded to your own specifications.- 1 round that is apparently an originally military round- 83 shell casings in apparent new condition- 187 Remington Corelokt 140-grain PSP bullets- set of RCBS 6.5x55 dies in excellent condition (RCBS #13201), in boxThe pictures here are just to whet your appetite, but I have many others and would be happy to take more if you want to see something specific. When you're ready, let me show you this beauty in person!I prefer a face-to-face deal for cash in the NW San Antonio / Helotes / Leon Springs area, but I'm willing to ship to a dealer at buyer's expense. Buy it from me and have it today – no sales tax, no dealer fees, etc. I will be offering a few other things, so check out my other listings and let's make a deal!PENDING SALE
